It haunts me.

228
00:21:00,783 --> 00:21:02,774
All of it.

229
00:21:02,863 --> 00:21:07,254
If you think that I would add
to the body count now, you are crazy.

230
00:21:07,343 --> 00:21:12,895
So you go looking for drunk co-eds
cos you're hungry for conversation?

231
00:21:12,983 --> 00:21:16,134
- Oh, is that what this is? Right.
- What?

232
00:21:16,223 --> 00:21:19,659
- You're jealous.
- Don't play games. Not now.

233
00:21:19,743 --> 00:21:23,941
You saw me chatting up another bird,
giving the eye to somebody else.

234
00:21:24,023 --> 00:21:27,538
- Touched a nerve, didn't it?
- Don't flatter yourself.

235
00:21:27,623 --> 00:21:33,573
It burns. But you can't admit it, so you trump
up some charge that I'm back on the juice.

236
00:21:33,663 --> 00:21:38,453
- This vampire I killed told me...
- Told you what? That I go out?

237
00:21:38,543 --> 00:21:41,899
Yeah, I talk to people. Women.

238
00:21:41,983 --> 00:21:46,659
- I talk to them cos I can't talk to you.
- Oh, Spike, save it.

239
00:21:46,743 --> 00:21:49,655
As daft a notion as
"soulful Spike the killer" is,

240
00:21:49,743 --> 00:21:55,295
it is nothing compared to the idea that
another girl could mean anything to me.

241
00:21:56,183 --> 00:21:59,812
This chip... they did <i>to</i> me.

242
00:21:59,903 --> 00:22:01,939
I couldn't help it.

243
00:22:02,023 --> 00:22:04,981
But the soul, I got on my own.

244
00:22:05,063 --> 00:22:07,054
For you.

245
00:22:10,583 --> 00:22:14,781
- I know. But...
- So, yeah. I go and pass the time.

246
00:22:14,863 --> 00:22:16,694
With someone.

247
00:22:16,783 --> 00:22:22,335
But that's all it is, is time. Cos God help me,
Buffy, it's still all about you.

248
00:22:25,303 --> 00:22:29,581
- Spike, this vampire told me you sired him.
- That doesn't mean...

249
00:22:29,663 --> 00:22:33,133
He said you killed him,
dumped him in a parking lot somewhere.

250
00:22:33,223 --> 00:22:37,614
- And you believed him? Vampires aren't...
- I did follow you last night.

251
00:22:37,703 --> 00:22:42,219
You didn't look lonely or casual to me.
You looked like you were on the prowl.

252
00:22:42,303 --> 00:22:45,852
- You can't know that.
- So, then, tell me. Tell me what happened.

253
00:22:45,943 --> 00:22:49,379
- You talked to her, then what?
- We talked. That's all I remember.

254
00:22:49,463 --> 00:22:52,216
- All you remember?
- I don't know. I go out.

255
00:22:52,303 --> 00:22:57,058
I talk to people or I don't.
It's boring. It all bleeds together.

256
00:22:57,143 --> 00:23:00,055
- Well, if you seem to forget that much...
- Not that.

257
00:23:00,143 --> 00:23:03,453
The taste of human blood.
That, I'd remember.

258
00:23:03,543 --> 00:23:08,663
You were camped out on the Hellmouth
talking to invisible people. Recently.

259
00:23:08,743 --> 00:23:12,053
- How can you be sure of...
- No! You are wrong.

260
00:23:12,143 --> 00:23:17,775
You've got an accusation
from a pile of dust, and not a shred of proof.

261
00:23:17,863 --> 00:23:20,331
So I'll get some.

262
00:23:31,143 --> 00:23:34,658
OK, guys, find me some evidence
that he did this.

263
00:23:34,743 --> 00:23:40,101
- Really? Are you sure that's what you want?
- Find me proof that he didn't.

264
00:23:40,183 --> 00:23:44,461
You only think Spike is turning people
cos that vampire told you so, right?

265
00:23:44,543 --> 00:23:49,139
But that night,
we were all told things that weren't true.

266
00:23:49,223 --> 00:23:50,975
Maybe.

267
00:23:51,063 --> 00:23:53,531
What? What "maybe"?

268
00:23:53,623 --> 00:23:57,616
Just because those weren't
the spirits of, you know, our people,

269
00:23:57,703 --> 00:24:02,140
just because it was some evil thing,
doesn't mean what they said can't be true.

270
00:24:02,223 --> 00:24:06,057
I used to tell the truth all the time
when I was evil.

271
00:24:06,143 --> 00:24:08,782
We can't assume anything.
We need hard facts.

272
00:24:08,863 --> 00:24:13,732
If Spike is biting people again, shouldn't
there be more dead people with neck trauma?

273
00:24:13,823 --> 00:24:17,133
Right? And we can find that.

274
00:24:17,223 --> 00:24:19,691
- No.
- No, we can't find that? But that's easy.

275
00:24:19,783 --> 00:24:21,580
That computer's a moron.

276
00:24:21,663 --> 00:24:27,579
I mean, no, there's not really
an increase in neck injuries. But...

277
00:24:27,663 --> 00:24:29,540
But what?

278
00:24:29,623 --> 00:24:32,660
Missing people. Eight, maybe.

279
00:24:33,303 --> 00:24:35,339
Oh, ten of them.

280
00:24:35,423 --> 00:24:38,938
No bodies, they're just missing.

281
00:24:39,023 --> 00:24:41,332
Mostly young. Lots of girls.

282
00:24:42,823 --> 00:24:48,739
So it's true. What that vampire
told Buffy turned out to be true.

283
00:24:48,823 --> 00:24:50,734
Maybe.

284
00:24:50,823 --> 00:24:53,815
But it still doesn't prove that it's Spike.

285
00:24:53,903 --> 00:24:57,612
Right now,
he's the only one who knows for sure.

286
00:25:27,063 --> 00:25:30,294
- No, no, no. You're not going out.
- I have to go.

287
00:25:30,383 --> 00:25:32,613
Buffy was very clear
on the not leaving of you.

288
00:25:32,703 --> 00:25:36,742
I know what she told you. It's not true.
Let me go, and I'll find a way to prove it.

289
00:25:36,823 --> 00:25:39,974
OK, I'm gonna list the reasons
that won't happen. One...

290
00:25:40,543 --> 00:25:41,862
Ow!

291
00:25:49,503 --> 00:25:52,301
<i>(# "This Is How It Goes" by Aimee Mann)</i>

292
00:26:31,983 --> 00:26:37,011
She had blonde hair. A nice-looking girl.
I was here talking with her.

293
00:26:37,623 --> 00:26:41,218
The other night. I'm looking for
someone who might've seen her.

294
00:26:41,303 --> 00:26:43,294
No. Sorry.

295
00:27:04,143 --> 00:27:06,896
- He hit you?
- Knocked me out.

296
00:27:06,983 --> 00:27:11,420
- He's been gone at least half an hour.
- Any idea where he's headed?

297
00:27:11,503 --> 00:27:14,301
<i>(# "Pavlov's Bell" by Aimee Mann)</i>

298
00:27:21,743 --> 00:27:24,621
One of 'em take your wallet?

299
00:27:26,063 --> 00:27:27,382
What's that?

300
00:27:27,463 --> 00:27:31,661
The way you're scanning that crowd.
You look like you're out for blood.

301
00:27:31,743 --> 00:27:37,693
I'm just looking for a certain bird
I met here the other night.

302
00:27:38,703 --> 00:27:42,252
- Is it me?
- Sorry, love. Don't think so.

303
00:27:43,583 --> 00:27:46,177
Not even if I ask nice?

304
00:27:49,303 --> 00:27:53,740
Or are you the type that has to be convinced?

305
00:27:53,823 --> 00:27:57,259
Friendly warning, pet.
I'm the type best left alone.

306
00:27:57,343 --> 00:28:00,096
Oh. I get it.

307
00:28:00,183 --> 00:28:04,381
You'd rather I slip into
something more comfortable.

308
00:28:07,463 --> 00:28:12,173
Shall we pick off the crowd one by one,
or block the exits and ravish the place?

309
00:28:12,263 --> 00:28:15,733
- Get away from me.
- What's with the wallflower act?

310
00:28:15,823 --> 00:28:19,179
You didn't seem so shy
when you were biting me.

311
00:28:21,543 --> 00:28:27,539
I'm not asking if you wanna be soul mates.
Just figured you'd wanna have some fun.

312
00:28:28,623 --> 00:28:29,692
Mm.

313
00:28:29,783 --> 00:28:34,937
I take him, you take her.
Or the other way around. Whatever.

314
00:28:35,463 --> 00:28:37,852
No, you're lying.

315
00:28:40,863 --> 00:28:43,502
Is that all I was to you? A one-bite stand?

316
00:29:57,543 --> 00:30:00,694
Hey, sweetheart.
If you wanna go in, go ahead.

317
00:30:00,783 --> 00:30:03,581
Actually, I need some help.
I'm looking for this guy.

318
00:30:03,663 --> 00:30:08,942
Bleach-blond hair, leather jacket, British
accent. Kind of sallow, but in a hot way?

319
00:30:09,023 --> 00:30:11,981
Yeah, yeah, I know the guy.
Billy Idol wannabe.

320
00:30:12,063 --> 00:30:16,375
Actually, Billy Idol stole his look from...
Never mind. Has he been here?

321
00:30:16,463 --> 00:30:19,057
This guy your boyfriend or something?

322
00:30:19,143 --> 00:30:23,421
No, I just... I need to find him,
as soon as possible.

323
00:30:23,503 --> 00:30:29,499
He comes in a lot lately. Every night leaves
with a different girl. Chicks like Billy Idol.

324
00:30:30,423 --> 00:30:32,653
How many girls?

325
00:30:32,743 --> 00:30:35,860
Look, this guy, this not-your-boyfriend guy.

326
00:30:35,943 --> 00:30:38,537
If I were you, I'd lose him.
He's a real player.

327
00:30:48,423 --> 00:30:51,495
Man, I hate playing vampire towns.

328
00:30:58,703 --> 00:31:00,694
Hello? It's me.

329
00:31:03,183 --> 00:31:05,299
I'm seeing...

330
00:31:05,383 --> 00:31:10,377
I think I'm remembering.
I think I've done some very bad things.

331
00:31:11,103 --> 00:31:12,695
Where are you?

332
00:31:12,783 --> 00:31:18,335
I need to see you. There's a house.
634 Hoffman Terrace.

333
00:31:18,423 --> 00:31:20,812
I'll meet you.

334
00:31:23,463 --> 00:31:25,579
You shouldn't have done that.

335
00:31:25,663 --> 00:31:27,779
It's not time yet.

336
00:31:27,863 --> 00:31:29,660
Not nearly.

337
00:31:29,743 --> 00:31:32,337
You're going against the plan.

338
00:31:33,223 --> 00:31:35,578
But we can make it work.

339
00:31:49,503 --> 00:31:51,494
Down here.

340
00:32:01,343 --> 00:32:03,732
You won't come down?

341
00:32:05,183 --> 00:32:07,253
I understand.

342
00:32:07,343 --> 00:32:10,141
It's a risky proposition.

343
00:32:10,223 --> 00:32:15,058
There's an order. The Slayer's not in order.
But it can't hurt to play.

344
00:32:15,143 --> 00:32:19,819
- Get your claws in the mouse, you know?
- You are not here.

345
00:32:28,983 --> 00:32:32,817
All right. What do you wanna show me?

346
00:32:32,903 --> 00:32:35,701
I've been remembering.

347
00:32:35,783 --> 00:32:38,661
The girl. I walked her home.

348
00:32:39,503 --> 00:32:42,176
The one you saw.

349
00:32:42,263 --> 00:32:44,857
And the one before that.

350
00:32:45,743 --> 00:32:48,541
And I think I killed her.

351
00:32:48,623 --> 00:32:53,697
And I think I... I think I killed...
the lady who lived here.

352
00:32:54,543 --> 00:32:57,933
And... and there might be others.

353
00:33:00,663 --> 00:33:02,381
Oh, my God.

354
00:33:03,343 --> 00:33:05,140
Here.

355
00:33:09,423 --> 00:33:12,142
I-I think I buried them here.

356
00:33:14,743 --> 00:33:16,495
Spike, why?

357
00:33:16,583 --> 00:33:20,258
Well, I don't know, do I?
I don't even know how. I shouldn't be able...

358
00:33:20,343 --> 00:33:24,575
<i># Early one morning
just as the sun was rising

359
00:33:24,663 --> 00:33:29,134
<i># I heard a fair maid sing
in the valley down below

360
00:33:29,583 --> 00:33:32,097
- <i># Oh, don't deceive me
- What? What is it?

361
00:33:32,183 --> 00:33:34,617
<i># Oh, never leave me

362
00:33:34,703 --> 00:33:38,332
<i># How could you use a poor maid...

363
00:33:38,423 --> 00:33:39,776
Spike!

364
00:33:45,903 --> 00:33:48,292
What are you doing? Oh!

365
00:33:51,583 --> 00:33:53,938
Spike, listen to me. You don't wanna do this.

366
00:33:55,183 --> 00:33:57,538
And it's just about to get fun.

367
00:34:05,423 --> 00:34:06,412
Oh, God.

368
00:34:20,383 --> 00:34:22,533
You know what I want you to do.

369
00:34:33,823 --> 00:34:38,419
They're waiting for you.
Take her, taste her. Make her weak.

370
00:34:41,663 --> 00:34:43,540
Spike, no!

371
00:35:16,103 --> 00:35:18,059
I remember.

372
00:35:42,783 --> 00:35:45,092
You failed them.

373
00:35:46,103 --> 00:35:48,378
Now she's gonna kill you.

374
00:35:48,463 --> 00:35:50,215
You lose, mate.

375
00:35:54,623 --> 00:35:57,695
Sorry, ma'am, but it's my job.

376
00:36:31,823 --> 00:36:34,212
Do it fast, OK?

377
00:36:36,783 --> 00:36:38,774
He said you would do it.

378
00:36:38,863 --> 00:36:40,854
Who said?

379
00:36:42,383 --> 00:36:44,180
Me.

380
00:36:45,503 --> 00:36:47,494
It was me.

381
00:36:48,543 --> 00:36:50,773
I saw it.

382
00:36:50,863 --> 00:36:54,538
I was here the whole time,
talking and singing.

383
00:36:56,583 --> 00:36:58,778
There was a song.

384
00:36:59,703 --> 00:37:03,332
- What are you talking about?
- I don't know.

385
00:37:03,423 --> 00:37:05,937
Please, I don't remember.

386
00:37:06,023 --> 00:37:08,412
Don't make me remember.

387
00:37:09,903 --> 00:37:13,896
Make it so I forget again!
I did what you wanted!

388
00:37:16,663 --> 00:37:19,131
There's something here.

389
00:37:24,183 --> 00:37:27,255
Oh God, no. Please. I need that.

390
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:31,336
I can't cry this soul out of me.

391
00:37:31,423 --> 00:37:33,857
It won't come.

392
00:37:34,343 --> 00:37:37,062
I've killed, and I can feel them.

393
00:37:38,103 --> 00:37:40,901
I can feel every one of 'em.

394
00:37:49,223 --> 00:37:52,135
There's something playing with us.

395
00:37:52,223 --> 00:37:54,020
All of us.

396
00:37:59,623 --> 00:38:01,853
What is it?

397
00:38:01,943 --> 00:38:04,411
Why is it doing this to me?

398
00:38:05,663 --> 00:38:07,460
I don't know.

399
00:38:12,383 --> 00:38:14,055
Help me.

400
00:38:17,583 --> 00:38:19,380
Can you help me?

401
00:38:22,663 --> 00:38:24,654
<i>(Buffy)</i> I'll help you.

402
00:38:29,383 --> 00:38:31,692
<i>(Anya)</i> And you believe him?

403
00:38:31,783 --> 00:38:36,299
<i>(Buffy)</i> You didn't see him down there.
He really didn't know what he'd done.

404
00:38:36,383 --> 00:38:38,692
It wasn't in his control.

405
00:38:38,783 --> 00:38:42,935
Oh, an out-of-control serial killer.
You're right, that <i>is</i> a great house guest.

406
00:38:43,023 --> 00:38:46,379
Wait. Is he... is he staying here?

407
00:38:46,463 --> 00:38:50,820
I don't know. But I'm not letting him
out of my sight, that's for sure.

408
00:38:50,903 --> 00:38:54,498
Buffy, he's been feeding on human blood.
That's gotta do stuff.

409
00:38:54,583 --> 00:38:58,132
I'm not keeping him around just to help him.

410
00:38:58,223 --> 00:39:02,535
I think there was something there,
talking to him, making him do things.

411
00:39:02,623 --> 00:39:05,456
Something like what was talking to us?

412
00:39:05,543 --> 00:39:09,900
Maybe. And if it was, then it's been
screwing with Spike big time.

413
00:39:09,983 --> 00:39:12,258
So, you want him around because...?

414
00:39:12,343 --> 00:39:14,652
There's something evil working us,

415
00:39:14,743 --> 00:39:19,100
and to have a chance to fight it,
we need to learn everything we can about it.

416
00:39:19,183 --> 00:39:22,061
This thing has been
closer to Spike than any of us.

417
00:39:22,143 --> 00:39:26,978
- And if you wanna understand it...
- I'm gonna have to get close to Spike.

418
00:39:27,063 --> 00:39:29,497
- It's too dangerous.
- <i>(Buffy)</i> I don't have a choice.

419
00:39:29,583 --> 00:39:32,416
Whatever this thing is from beneath us,

420
00:39:32,503 --> 00:39:34,971
it's bad,

421
00:39:35,063 --> 00:39:38,180
and it's only getting worse.

422
00:39:46,343 --> 00:39:48,334
Oh, dear God!

423
00:39:51,303 --> 00:39:53,692
Robson, are you here?

424
00:39:55,343 --> 00:39:57,174
Robson?

425
00:39:57,263 --> 00:39:59,060
<i>(groaning)</i>

426
00:40:05,423 --> 00:40:07,983
You too?

427
00:40:15,423 --> 00:40:18,301
- Dear God, I thought you were...
- Gather them.

428
00:40:18,383 --> 00:40:20,977
- What?
- It's started.

429
00:40:21,743 --> 00:40:24,940
It's all right. I understand.
I'll take care...

